<br>
In my rudimentary tests taunt did seem to add agro. Go to a mob, hit taunt once, have caster tash, see if it switches to him. Now go to same mob, hit taunt once, wait for it to refresh, hit it again, have caster tash, see if it switches. Ofcourse dont melee or disarm or slam or anything for the test, just taunt. Simple test and it showed me taunt adds hate while you have agro and mashing is always the way to go.<br>
<br>
So can we have some empirical tests or data showing how taunt doesn't add hate while you have agro, since we already got all the smug comments like &quot;oh too many mashers&quot; &quot;if you go anything but #2 you don't know how taunt works&quot;. Well please enlighten us, how does it work ?<br>
<br>
-Desi of Wraith<br>
