<br>
Yes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>mashing is always the way to go.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Taunt adds a variable amount of hate when you pass the skill check. To the top of the aggro list + a small amount. That is how it works. This means that when used while you have aggro you gain the smallest amount of hate possible. When used when you are at the bottom of the list you gain the most amount of aggro. <br>
<br>
The amount of aggro you gain over the next highest person is small so small that said person could gain aggro back from you without a thought.<br>
<br>
The other things to consider: taunt is not 100%, you can and will fail the check constantly. Taunt is on a timer.<br>
<br>
That means if you gray taunt then someone gains aggro off of you must wait longer until you can taunt off of them. This leads to greater expenditures of mana on the casters behalf to reduce aggro or heal and less dps caused by monks and rogues as they try and dump aggro back on to you, all because you used taunt as a gimp aggro generation tool.<br>
<br>
Just say no to mashing.<br>
