<br>
Like someone said, why have enraging blow weapons, weapons with higher aggro proc then others, if when youre at top, you cant get any higher, imo it wouldnt be to regain taunt then since you can just push taunt (most spells aggro &lt; 2 taunts).<br>
<br>
Why also does a melee have to BUILD aggro on a mob before everyone engages ? He is at top of aggro list since he is only one attacking so logically why lose time since he cant get any higher ?<br>
You could say for vinid, tank has to be only to tank before mob is slowed so if any ranger etc overtaunts he doesnt die immediatly. Some other mobs on other hand, cant be slowed and you still need to wait till MA gets aggro which goes totally against what is said about being first on list and you cant get any higher.<br>
<br>
IMO that would mean there is an aggro cap which isnt logical since at one moment everyone aggro adds and thus everyone will be at same number, the cap so everyone at same aggro lvl thus why have a MT since everyone has same chance to get hit.<br>
<br>
More logical, still IMO is there is no aggro cap. I dunno number but say you have an enraging blow weapon for 900 aggro, a FB for 300 aggro and taunt for 150 aggro. Snare is 250 aggro, slow 300 for ex, CH 450. (just examples no idea on what numbers it would be).<br>
Then you understand why warrior has to BUILD aggro.<br>
mob snared = - 250<br>
taunt = 150  ..  snare still has aggro at - 100<br>
taunt = 150  ..  snare loses aggro at + 50<br>
proc EB weapon = 900<br>
proc FB = 300<br>
taunt = 150<br>
proc FB = 300<br>
taunt = 150<br>
Mob is slowed = - 900  ..  warrior has 2100 - 900 = + 1200 doesnt lose aggro<br>
taunt = 150<br>
taunt = 150<br>
warrior has build 2400 aggro now and will continue to gain it during fight. If someone outaggros his melee fight aggro + procs during it + taunts then he will still have 2400 reserve aggro so he doesnt lose aggro.<br>
<br>
that doesnt include any dps<br>
<br>
That shows my point. The more you taunt the more you save aggro. At same time if you dont taunt you might still keep aggro if youre aggro &gt; aggro of each group member. But there is nothing in the Pool if someone outaggros you. Thats when some taunt to regain aggro.<br>
<br>
That also shows why a warrior with crap weapons will lose a lot more aggro then one with and thats why he will need MORE time to aggro before everyone engages so he has a high enough Pool of aggro to compensate. Thats also why, if fight is too long, he will lose aggro at one time.<br>
<br>
This might be totally false but thats the reason which makes me think its better to always taunt when youre MT. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
