<br>
Taunt is not 150.<br>
<br>
Try this on for size and see if it makes it any clearer: <br>
<br>
Taunt <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>changes</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> your hate value directly to the highest person on the lists aggo score + a small amount. <br>
<br>
That is how it works, it  does not add + X Hate like a proc. It changes your aggro directly to Y hate. Just like memblur changes your aggro to 0 hate. It is a direct change for all or nothing.<br>
<br>
By pushing taunt when you have aggro you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>change</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> your number of hate to your number of hate with just enough extra aggro for a mob to switch targets from you too you. Grats, you just taunted off of yourself. <br>
<br>
You all should know how much it takes for whoever you taunted off of to gain aggro back after you taunt off of them that’s how much hate you just gained, next to nothing.<br>
<br>
So changing your hate for a split seconds worth more or getting aggro off of someone 6 seconds sooner. The button is yours.<br>
